A new era in air transportation has arrived, borne on the
wings of Pan American's new double-decked "America"-class
Clipper. Biggest commercial landplane in the world, this
impressive newcomer is years ahead in design, engineering
and performance. From the passenger's viewpoint, comfort,
speed and security have been combined to a degree un-
dreamed of only a few months ago.
Built and perfected by the same manufacturer who pro-
duced the war-time B-17 and B-29 bombers, the "America"-
class Clipper is the commercial version of the non-stop
world-girding B-50 Superfort. This double-decked, luxury
airliner will turn previously tiresome inter-continental jour-
neys into brief flights of utmost comfort and convenience.
The vast Atlantic and Pacific oceans will now be spanned in
many hours less than ever before... the long flight between
the United States and Rio de Janeiro or Buenos Aires will
be cut by as much as half a day.
In 1949 alone, twenty of the "America"-class Clippers
will be carrying the flag of the United States, establishing
new records for speed and distance all over the world.
Pan American's Round-the- World Route together with
the network that serves 73 countries and colonies will come
to know the majestic sight of these unrivalled double-decked
champions of the skyways of tomorrow.
